article.description: — Jamaree Bouyea scored 20 points and Dzmitry Ryuny had 18 points and 10 rebounds as San Francisco beat Towson 79-68 on Thursday.
article.headline: Bouyea scores 20 to lead San Francisco over Towson 79-68
article.linkText: Bouyea scores 20 to lead San Francisco over Towson 79-68
article.story: UNCASVILLE, Conn. -- — Jamaree Bouyea scored 20 points and Dzmitry Ryuny had 18 points and 10 rebounds as San Francisco beat Towson 79-68 on Thursday. Damari Milstead added 11 points and Samba Kane had 10 points for San Francisco (1-1). Khalil Shabazz, who scored 31 points in the opener, was held to five points on 2-of-11 shooting. Zane Martin had 25 points for the Tigers (0-2). Nicolas Timberlake added 12 points and Victor Uyaelunmo had 11 points and 10 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
